PrismLauncher (An Open Source Minecraft launcher)

An Open Source Minecraft launcher with the ability to manage multiple
instances, accounts and mods. Focused on user freedom and free
redistributability.

A Microsoft or Mojang account that owns Minecraft is required to
download and play the game through PrismLauncher.

To build PrismLauncher you can use any JDK version (8..25) and variant
(Oracle JDK, OpenJDK, Zulu OpenJDK). Keep in mind, however, that in
order to run different mods and Minecraft versions you may need
different Java versions. PrismLauncher includes Java downloader which
you can use to install an appropriate version locally.

26.1 and newer:    JRE 25
1.20.5 to 1.21.11: JRE 21
1.17 to 1.20.4:    JRE 17
1.16 or older:     JRE 8

Optional dependencies are:
- scdoc: if present at build time, a man page for PrismLauncher will be
         generated
- glfw3: use system GLFW libraries
- flite: narrator support
- orca:  screen reader support
